RECOMMENDED VAxAI ENTRY: Blend: AI training + automation + selective VA

WHY ADMIN / AI PRESSURE IS HIGH:
Policy renewal chasing, claims FNOL intake, insurer correspondence, MTA processing, client fact-finds, compliance file reviews, and commission reconciliation across multiple insurers.

UK AI ADOPTION (use in conversation):
Barclays Business Prosperity Index (Aug 2025): 89% of UK businesses plan AI use within two years; SMEs (10–49 staff) averaged £125k AI investment vs £400k for 250+ employee firms. Lloyds Business Barometer (Mar 2026): 66% have invested in AI, mostly under £25k—39% cite AI/digital skills shortage. Insurance brokers digitised policy admin but AI for claims triage and renewal risk analysis is early among regional brokers.

WHERE VA ALONE IS NOT THE RIGHT LEAD:
VA not lead for regulated advice or claims FNOL needing structured data capture—automate intake forms first.

SUGGESTED CALL HOOKS / DISCOVERY QUESTIONS:
• AI renewal risk summaries
• Automate MTA paperwork
• Train brokers on AI market comparisons

DISCOVERY PROMPTS FOR THIS CALL:
• How much time does the team spend on the highest-volume admin tasks in insurance brokers?
• Have they piloted AI tools internally, or only client-facing tech?
• Who owns operations/process improvement — and is AI training on anyone''s KPIs?
• What would ''win'' look like in 90 days: hours saved, fewer errors, or staff confident using AI?

NOTES:
Revenue/employee figures are estimates for sizing only — confirm on Companies House before quoting.
Research date: 2026-06-23. Validate website and decision-maker before outreach.

